title: Starting Skins CBs Hall, Culliver out; TE Reed expected back
text:
Starting Skins CBs Hall, Culliver out; TE Reed expected back By -   
ASHBURN, Va. (AP) - Washington Redskins cornerbacks DeAngelo Hall and Chris Culliver, receiver DeSean Jackson and center Kory Lichtensteiger will miss Sundayâ€™s game against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers because of injuries. 
All four of those starters were sidelined last week, too: Hall by a toe problem, Culliver a knee, Jackson a hamstring and Lichtensteiger a thumb. 
Two other starters were listed Friday as questionable by coach Jay Gruden because of concussions - left tackle Trent Williams and tight end Jordan Reed - but he said both are expected to be fully cleared and available against the Bucs. 
Running back Chris Thompson was listed as doubtful with a bruised back after missing practice Friday.
